  "abstract": "Aided language modelling (ALM), while using responsive partner strategies and a gaze-controlled device may be used with adult individuals with Rett syndrome to increase their rate of expressive communication. Detailed observational measures revealed individual learning patterns, which may provide clinically valuable insights.Implications for RehabilitationAdults with Rett syndrome may benefit from access to gaze-controlled devices in combination with responsive partner strategies.Responsive partner communication may be effective for some individuals with Rett syndrome to increase their rate of synthesised utterances.Rate of focused gazes may be considered as an outcome measure for individuals with oculomotor difficulties when introducing aided language modelling.",
